originalText.text: This was one of my mother's favorite senior centers to attend the atmosphere is so welcoming the people are so friendly you feel at home there if you are a person that lives in New York City and you live alone you should definitely check out the Kennedy Center they make you part of their home

originalText.text:
I am very disappointed to have to agree with many of the negative review comments about the reception, and rude unprofessionalism over the phone. I could only imagine how they treat people in person.  First off, the receptionist Karen (if that's her name because I find it ironic and funny) was so rude and bothered by my call and really disgusting personality on the phone. Heaven help me, if I was there in person having our conversation. She appeared very bothered and it was only 11:40 in the morning. Secondly, I grew up in this Center, in the late 70's and early 80's. I find it hard to believe that a Well Popular Center in the African American community that was run by community members who lived in the area, is now... Well what is has become.  No one was ever rude at the reception and what they have going on now, must need some fine tuning and training in professional etiquette.  How "Karen" is the receptionist is hard to believe, she really does not like being there, or her job.  I really hope the Present Center Director takes time to address her poor attitude since she is the first face you meet on the phone or in person.
Signed,
"Previous Child Member of what helped shape my Adulthood".
...Sadly disappointed in what it has become. Not a very Welcoming reception.

originalText.text:
This place is way bigger that I thought. It is amazing that they have a cooling location for people in the heat that we have been experiencing lately. They also are very thorough during this crisis and making sure everyone stays safe. I really appreciate that.

I honestly would have given them 5 stars if it wasn't for an incident where someone destroyed one of the women's restrooms. They are great about cleaning up promptly don't get me wrong but I just cant get passed that.
